  "response": "Kilauea, located on the Big Island of Hawaii, is often considered the world's most active volcano. It has been erupting almost continuously from 1983 to 2018, and had another significant eruption in 2021. Located in Hawaii Volcanoes National Park, Kilauea is known for its frequent and relatively accessible lava flows. However, some volcanoes like Stromboli in Italy are also known for near-constant activity and are sometimes referred to as the \"Lighthouse of the Mediterranean\" due to their persistent eruptions.",
